abstract: AT&T reported a 17 percent increase in quarterly profits driven by a sizable increase in wireless subscribers.
snippet: AT&T reported a 17 percent increase in quarterly profits driven by a sizable increase in wireless subscribers.
lead_paragraph: Capping a whirlwind year of merging and rebranding that has come to characterize the telecommunications business, AT&T reported a 17 percent increase in quarterly profits yesterday driven by a sizable increase in wireless subscribers.

headline.main: Gains in Wireless Customers Help Lift AT&T’s Earnings 17%
headline.print_headline: Gains in Wireless Customers Help Lift AT&T’s Earnings 17%
